		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Newbie Warrrior guide, level 1-10<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Mar 30th 12:42 AM 2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=98593096764434&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=1&mid=98593096764434&num=1&page=&post=1&replyto=98593096764434"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>   <a name=98593096764434></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=33706"><span id=>Kildaar</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br>37 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.90]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Alright, this is for all you people out there that can&#8217;t wander off on your own and play the game like it was supposed to be played, didn&#8217;t mean to flame anyone.&nbsp;&nbsp;As for all you newbies out there you may come into the world and be utterly confused, well cheer up, I&#8217;m here to help you.<br><br>Kildaar is a currently level 11 Dwarf Warrior, I chose a Dwarf because I liked the stats and I was influenced by another Dwarf Warrior out there on the Druzzil Ro server, I won&#8217;t post his name cause I don&#8217;t know if he wants his name up here or not.  Anywho before you create your character go to www.eqatlas.com and print the map of your city and any zones you will be visiting, this is to prevent you from getting lost in the huge world EQ has to offer.  Trust me, there is nothing worse than getting lost and losing your corpse at such a tender age.  Second is to print this guide so you may look at it later for reference if needed.  Third is to have fun, that&#8217;s what this game is all about and I&#8217;ll be damned if you don&#8217;t follow the third step.<br><br>Before I even begin with the guide part I must first tell you that unlike most other games this game is not linear.  (for the younger crowd linear means that the game would have one path and there is no way to branch off.)  There are many different ways to play this game and I&#8217;m just telling you the way I chose to play it.  Now on the fun stuff.<br><br>Level 1-2 ~ Stay outside you home city, just over the hill in Kaladim hunting worker scarabs, goblin whelps, snakes, and decaying skeletons.  In Kelethin stay by the newbie lift and hunt bats and decaying skellies by the druid ring, (think that&#8217;s what it&#8217;s called)<br><br>Level 3-5 ~ hunt orcs on orc hill, IMPORTANT stay with a group, if you wander off you will be killed by the dozens of orc centurions wandering about.  You could also kill skunks and other such things that con blue or white in BB.  *Hint if your coming from Butcherblok or Kaladim, get bound at one of the lifts.  (When you get bound you respawn there when you die, lots of help)<br><br>Level 6-10 ~ Now you should enter Crushbone, the last stronghold of the Crushbone Orcs.  This can be a very dangerous place so follow these rules:<br><br>1.Watch out for trains and wandering groups of orcs.<br>2. Don&#8217;t rely on others to get you out of trouble, always /con you foe before you attack.<br>3. Always /shout if you are leading a train to the tunnel entrance<br>4. Don&#8217;t drag too many trains to the tunnel entrance.<br><br>I&#8217;m level 11 now and am trying to get that elusive Shiny brass shield but so far with no luck.  Another good place to hunt would be the slaver pits to the east or the slaver caves and huts to the west.  There is also a legionnaire camp to the north but that should be for levels 11-15.<br><br>This concludes my guide for a beginning warrior and if I get enough requests for more info I&#8217;ll post it up here later.  If you have any questions comments please e-mail me at SecretSQ5@hotmail.com or just post replies on this forum.  Thanks for your time and I hope to write more of these guides in the future.<br></p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Kildaar<br>Druzzil Ro<br>Dwarven Warrior<br>15th season<br></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
